root.pub-comments: "In this altas, the Chinese language is divided into ten dialect groups: Mandarin Supergroup; Jin Group; Wu Group; Hui Group; Gan Group; Xiang Group; Min Group; Yue Group; Pinghua Group; Hakka Group." The authors used 'Supergroup > Group > Subgroup > Cluster' as their original heirarchy. In our termonology, this is 'Subgroup > Language > Dialect Group > Dialect' where applicable. See the original source and the LL-MAP for more details regarding dialect locations and characteristics.
